Value by alpha¶

from pysal.viz.splot.mapping import vba_choropleth

/opt/conda/lib/python3.6/site-packages/pysal/model/spvcm/abstracts.py:10: UserWarning: The `dill` module is required to use the sqlite backend fully.
  from .sqlite import head_to_sql, start_sql
In [21]:
f, ax = plt.subplots(1, figsize=(12, 12))
db.plot(ax=ax, facecolor='none', edgecolor='red')
vba_choropleth(db['arturo_score'], db['Scored streets'], db,
                alpha_mapclassify=dict(classifier='quantiles', k=5),
                rgb_mapclassify=dict(classifier='quantiles', k=5),
                legend=True, cmap='viridis', ax=ax)
ax.set_title('')
plt.show()
